import React, { useEffect, useState } from "react"; const SummaryStats = () => { const [summary, setSummary] = useState(null); const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true); const [error, setError] = useState(null); useEffect(() => { fetch("http://localhost:5000/summary/") .then((response) => response.json()) // fetch requires json() .then((data) => { console.log("API response:", data); setSummary(data); setLoading(false); }) .catch((err) => { console.error(err); setError("Error fetching summary stats"); setLoading(false); }); }, []); if (loading) return

Loading summary statistics...

; if (error) return

{error}

; if (!summary || !summary.overall_stats || !summary.top_brands) return

No data available

; return (

Overall Spend Statistics

Metric Value
Total Spend ${summary.overall_stats.total_spend.toFixed(2)}
Average Transaction ${summary.overall_stats.avg_transaction_amount.toFixed(2)}
Max Spend ${summary.overall_stats.max_spend.toFixed(2)}
Min Spend ${summary.overall_stats.min_spend.toFixed(2)}
Number of Transactions {summary.overall_stats.num_transactions}

Top Brands by Spend

{summary.top_brands.map((brand) => ( ))}
Brand Total Spend Average Spend Transactions
{brand.brand_name} ${brand.total_spend.toFixed(2)} ${brand.avg_spend.toFixed(2)} {brand.num_transactions}

Spend by Industry

{summary.spend_by_industry.map((row) => ( ))}
Industry Total Spend
{row.industry_name} ${row.total_spend.toFixed(2)}

Spend by State

{summary.spend_by_state.map((row) => ( ))}
State Total Spend
{row.state_abbr} ${row.total_spend.toFixed(2)}

Transaction Count by Industry

{summary.tx_count_by_industry.map((row) => ( ))}
Industry Transaction Count
{row.industry_name} {row.transaction_count}
); }; export default SummaryStats;
